article.headline: Austin Peay 73, Jacksonville St. 65
article.story: CLARKSVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Anthony Davis scored 16 points to lead Austin Peay to a 73-65 come-from-behind victory Tuesday night over Jacksonville State. The Governors (10-15, 8-5 Ohio Valley Conference) shot 66.7 percent in the second half to overcome a 38-30 halftime deficit. The Gamecocks (7-19, 2-11) helped Austin Peay by shooting just 36 percent in the final 20 minutes. Both teams shot at least 50 percent for the game. Austin Peay took its first lead with 6:36 to play on a 3-point shot by Maurice Hampton, who had 15 points. Jacksonville State, led by 25 points from B.J. Spencer who had seven 3-pointers, kept the game close until the Governors went on an 8-2 run capped by a William Durden basket with 2:17 left to take a 70-62 lead. Anthony Wilson, who had 14 points, hit a 3-pointer for the Gamecocks to make it 70-65, but Austin Peay hit its free throws in the final minute to clinch the game. Derek Wright and Durden both had 12 points for the Governors. Brandon Davis scored 12 points and had seven rebounds for Jacksonville State, while Walker Russell added 10 points.
